description.narrative: Government and civil society have improved capacity for (coordination, evidence generation and implementation of legislation ) the prevention and response to Violence against Children., which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Data And Child Protection, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By end of 2020, adolescent girls and boys aged 10-19 years have increased protection from violence and access to quality health services and secondary education.

description.narrative: National and regional capacity for coordination and data management systems on Violence Against Children (VAC) and Gender Based Violence prevention and response were enhanced through the comprehensive assessment of current systems, to inform recommendations for upgrade in 2020. The capacity to respond to VAC, and deal with child offenders and child victims of 412 (47%) child protection service providers from police and correctional services was enhanced through training on the Sexual Offenses and Domestic Violence Act (SODVA) and Child Protection Welfare Act (CPWA). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
